<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-12T23:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-12T23:54:00-05:00" n="743" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.51/67: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moose</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-13T08:00:00+03:06">April
                                        13, 1944—8 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>106. My 96, April 8, 9 a.m.<note n="62" xml:id="d743fn62">Not
                                    printed.</note> Both Saudi Finance Minister and Acting Foreign
                                Minister state that Saudi Government must have assistance in excess
                                of that contemplated in budget figures of British Minister.</p>
                            <p>They have indicated that they would like the United States to supply
                                deficiency. Request for specific sums expected in few days.</p>
                            <p>Sent Department, code text airmail to Cairo for Landis.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>